EXERCISE 4  
Answer the following questions:  
. What are the two reasons for spreading civilization?  
1
Ans: - The two reasons for spreading civilization are the invention of new machinery for the  
spreading of knowledge and increased ease of travel and communication.  
2
. What are the two effects of books?  
Ans: - The two effects of books are they preserve knowledge in time and spread it in space.  
3
. Why is knowledge compared to a torch?  
Ans: - Education is a means for passing on knowledge and ideas. Each fresh generation of  
people can be made acquainted with all the preceding generations have found out. Thus  
knowledge is like a torch which is passed on from generation to generation by the hands of  
education.  
4
. How was it possible for the ruling class to bully and oppress the mass of mankind?  
Ans: - The ruling class has been able to bully and oppress the mass of mankind because the  
rulers knew things which the masses did not, and this advantage in knowledge and power  
was partly due to the fact that the rulers could read.  
5
. Why are past civilizations said to be like a race?  
Ans: - Civilization in the past is said to be like a race because in it only a few of the runners  
has got right ahead of the others. At any moment they were liable to be pulled back to the  
level of the laggards and so the race for civilization was slowed down.  
6
. Who is a tolerant person?  
Ans: - A tolerant person is one who does not interfere with other people even if he thinks  
they are wrong but is prepared to let them think what they like and say what they think.  
7
. Why did people in the western world kill and torture other people?  
Ans: - In the western world, people killed and tortured other people because they did not  
believe the same things as they did or for worshipping god in a different way.  
8
. What did Charles Bradlaugh obtain in 1888?  
Ans: - Charles Bradlaugh obtained in 1888 the right to sit in the House of Commons without  
first swearing an oath in the name of God, in whom he did not believe.

EXERCISE 5  
Answer the following questions:  
. In what ways has science helped civilization to the world?  
1
Ans: - Science has helped civilization in many ways. In the past most of the civilization were  
confined to a small group of people, so they were at the risk of being pulled down by any  
barbaric group. With the invention of machinery like printing, education and wireless, what  
one people or even one man knows, spread through the world. Books are the chief carriers of  
civilization because of them ideas live and spread. By the means of education new  
generation of people can be made aware with all the preceding generation have found out.  
The coming of wireless was of great importance to civilization also, with its help people  
living in far-off places can watch events and know what is happening around the world.  
2
. What is the importance of books in bringing civilization?  
Ans: - Books play an important role in bringing civilization. they are the chief carriers of  
civilization because of them ideas live and spread. Where there are no books, there are no  
records and no literature. They preserve knowledge and spread it, without books it will be  
much more difficult for the race to progress and become civilized. Not only books could live  
in time, it could spread through space, by making enough copies of it and bring to the notice  
of hundreds and thousands of people until it is sent all over the world.  
COMPOSITION EXERCISES  
1
. Write a short paragraph dealing with three uses or effects of book?  
Ans: - In the past before the invention of printing and books, ideas and knowledge can only  
be handed down by word of mouth. Thus, it was much more difficult for any race to  
progress and spread their knowledge to other world. But with the invention of printing and  
book, knowledge can be preserved. Books could live in time for long by making enough  
copies of it and bring to notice of people all over the world.  
Page | 4  
2
. Write a short paragraph about three effects of the wireless.  
Ans: - Wireless brings people closer, those who lived in distant places and who have no time  
to read books, have only to turn on the loudspeaker to know what is happening around the  
world. Civilization in the past has been like a race in which only a few have got right ahead  
of the others. At any moment they were liable to be pulled back to the level of the laggards.  
But today there are fewer laggards and they are constantly being brought up to the levels of  
the others.  
3
. Write a short paragraph expressing what civilization is.  
Ans: - A civilization is generally defined as an advanced state of human society containing  
highly developed forms of government, culture, industry and common social norms. It is a  
form of government and symbolic systems of communication such as writing etc.  
4
. Write a paragraph on “Religious tolerance’’. Include the following points:  
a). what this means  
b). how this can be shown  
c). what happens in its absence  
Ans: - A tolerant person is one who does not interfere with other people. Intolerance was  
particularly common in religious matters. People had killed and tortured other people for not  
believing the same thing as they did or for worshipping God in a different way. Religious  
beliefs are based on faith. We cannot persuade other people to believe what we believe. If  
there is no tolerance in religion, people will be burnt alive and they will be punished for  
being different.
